== Afterwords

_holy peak that odds&ends foreshadowing from above..._

Hi, it's me. I feel uncomfortable using my real name, so let's go with my
Internet handle, _\@gbnam8_. I should really think up some sorts of a pen name
later, but whatever.

I am neither someone who has won any light novel competitions, nor a talented
writer who can form heart-wrenching stories. I don't have any editors,
illustrators nor mentors on this subject, only Internet videos of how to write a
novel. Even so, I had spent valuable time for the last year on this shitty novel
that no one will read, yet I didn't regret it one bit.

Honestly I would not have thought that this novel could reach that far. I
intended it to be short (my original outline has six chapters!), something like
the _Watashi, Idol Sengen_ novella. Now, it has become a full-fledged novel with a
huge cast of characters, and I am intending to write between 6 and 8 more
volumes. Seeing the characters in my novel going from a rough mental sketch in
my head to become breathing, living people in the story felt like seeing your
daughters growing up, an experience that I would likely not have for the rest of
my life.

For the "thank you" section, first, I would like to express my gratitude to
everyone in HoneyWorks, especially Mogelatte, the author of the _Watashi, Idol
  Sengen_ manga, for coming up with the original setting of the story.
_Confession Executive Committee_, despite much of my criticism for being
"overly-positive", was a very fascinating and compelling series, and Mona-chan,
being my so-called _waifu_, has been someone I really treasured throughout my
university life. The girl has been by my side for far longer than my classmates
or my lab mentor (who will soon appear in the series, stay tuned!), staying with
me through my deepest struggles.

The next on the list was a messy collection of anime shows I watched in the last
one or two years. Let's see. _BanG Dream! It's MyGO!!!!!_ and _Ave Mujica_,
_Girls Band Cry_, _Jellyfish Can't Swim in the Night_, _Happy Sugar Life_ and
_Takopii no Genzai_. All these works, as well as my miniscule real life
experiences, formed the basis for this work, with the center philosophy of
portraying everyone in a _gray-colored_ light. There are no bad guys, no good
guys, just people struggling in a broken world. This is why I hope that some of
you readers could bring yourself to hate Mona or Uta in the later volumes, as
these girls are written to have plenty of flaws within them. Even though they
were just reflections of myself (haha).

The first publication of this work is to be bundled along with _CTB Girls'
  Dormitory_'s (my one-man circle, ignore the cringe name, please)
Tea Party Album (I won't even say the real title here). Compared
to the writing here, the album's story was much less nuanced, and in that world,
"killing normies" seemed to be a perfectly valid excuse for executing
mass murder. Even though the lyrics were sloppy, the supernatural part was
never properly explained, and the singing was absolute trash, the album still
holds a special place in my heart. Though I prefer the more well-written stories
from the Suicide Album, I could not just glance over the enormous impact of Tea
Party Album on me. It will be released on the fall M3 of this year, three days
from the time of writing (I'm sorry for stalling!).

As for my final words, I hope you will continue to enjoy the never-ending
struggle of my past self.
